text.tspan: The share of adults aged 15 and older who can both read and write.
Note: Under the UNESCO metric, someone who is literate can, with understanding, read and write a short, simple statement on their everyday
life. However, definitions and criteria of literacy can vary by country. You can find further discussion on 'How is literacy measured?' in our post
